   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kepa&apos;s programme for 2013-2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kepa is an NGO platform and an expert on global development. At the moment Kepa has more than 300 member organisations, ranging from small voluntary-based organisations to major national organisations.

Kepa\&apos;s main objective for the 2013-2015 are: 
1) Along with its member organisations, Kepa influences political decision-making for eliminating poverty and inequality
2) In their common work, Kepa and its member organisations raise public awareness and increase public activity for a just world
3) Kepa builds capacity of its member organisations. 
The fourth main component of the programme consist of leadership, management and support functions. 

Through country and regional offices in Mekong, Mozambique, Nicaragua and Tanzania Kepa has extensive contacts with Southern civil society actors. Kepa aims to strengthen Southern civil societies by supporting civil
society actors&#x2019; competencies in advocacy themes and in the promotion of enabling operating environment as well as by supporting cooperation and networking at the national, regional and global levels. Cooperation with Southern civil society organisations (CSOs) provides Kepa with expertise, personal experiences and credibility.</narrative>
  </description>
